Over the weekend, I had the pleasure of managing the largest engagement I've ever managed in the duration of my career. @motherscookiesus took over downtown Plain City, just west of Columbus. In the past, I've managed 3 to 5 footprints at an event, however, I've never had one client BE THE EVENT. It was so unspeakably massive, that I had a staff of over 30 people, and a co-manager to help with the workload and initiative. I'm really grateful that I got to be a part of such a magical event! It was breathtaking and my team was AWESOME!!! So blessed to be working with such a crew! Can't wait to work with some of them again!

A few weeks ago, I was working in Vegas and staying at Caesars Palace. I didn't sleep much while I was there, but that wasn't the point. The last time I was at the Palace, I was working in racing. My life moves much faster than I could ever anticipate. There's no hesitation. There's always an objective that's so much bigger than me. I've dedicated my talent and skills to the "cutting edge" of every industry I've ever worked in. There's no rules or limitations to what I'm doing now. Just thankful that the person that I'm working with views the world in a similar fashion that I do. The next trip is very soon. But until then, I'll be in preproduction.
